https:\/\/t.co\/M95130vmCk","display_text_range":[0,160],"entities":{"hashtags":[],"urls":[{"url":"https:\/\/t.co\/mGf8fBJmrI","expanded_url":"https:\/\/www.medrxiv.org\/content\/10.1101\/2020.03.30.20048165v1","display_url":"medrxiv.org\/content\/10.110\u2026","unwound":{"url":"https:\/\/www.medrxiv.org\/content\/10.1101\/2020.03.30.20048165v1","status":200,"title":"Association of BCG vaccination policy with prevalence and mortality of COVID-19","description":"There is some evidence that tuberculosis vaccine bacillus Calmette-Gu\u00e9rin (BCG) has non-specific beneficial effects against non-related infections. Here, we examined the possible association between BCG vaccination with prevalence and mortality by COVID-19 by using publicly available data of COVID-19 in 199 countries\/regions and the BCG World Atlas. By using linear regression modeling, we found that the number of total cases and deaths per one million population were significantly associated with the country's policy concerning BCG vaccine administration. The amount of variance in cases and deaths explained by BCG vaccination policy ranged between 12.5% and 38%. Importantly, this effect remained significant after controlling for the country's life expectancy and the average temperature in February and March 2020, which themselves are significantly correlated with the cases and deaths indices, respectively. of BCG vaccination policy with prevalence and mortality of COVID-19","description":"There is some evidence that tuberculosis vaccine bacillus Calmette-Gu\u00e9rin (BCG) has non-specific beneficial effects against non-related infections. Here, we examined the possible association between BCG vaccination with prevalence and mortality by COVID-19 by using publicly available data of COVID-19 in 199 countries\/regions and the BCG World Atlas. By using linear regression modeling, we found that the number of total cases and deaths per one million population were significantly associated with the country's policy concerning BCG vaccine administration. The amount of variance in cases and deaths explained by BCG vaccination policy ranged between 12.5% and 38%. Importantly, this effect remained significant after controlling for the country's life expectancy and the average temperature in February and March 2020, which themselves are significantly correlated with the cases and deaths indices, respectively. By contrast, the ratio between deaths and cases was weakly affected.
